\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b Que1. What is API Testing and why Postman is most popular tool for API Testing?\par
Ans1= API Testing: \b0 API Testing is used to validates Application Programming Interfaces (APIs). The purpose of API Testing is to check the functionality, reliability, performance, and security of the programming interfaces. In API Testing, instead of using standard user inputs(keyboard) and outputs, we use software to send calls to the API, get output, and note down the system\rquote s response. \par
\b Postman: \b0 Postman is a collaboration platform for API development. It is a recognized API client that enables us to organize the creation, division, testing, and documentation of APIs.\par
Postman is most popular tool for API Testing because,\par
1. API Client feature lets us send REST, SOAP requests directly quickly within Postman.\par
2. It ensures safe automation and integration of manual tests that guarantee no code breaks.\par
3. It enables us to design and mock the responses of an API without having to set up a backend server.\par
4. Machine-readable documentation.\par
5. Monitor the API performance and response times at regular intervals.\par
6. The built-in version control lets us share and collaborate in real-time.\par
\b\par
