Que3. What are the different http methods for API Testing?\par
Ans3= The different http methods for API Testing are:\par
GET: \b0 GET method is used to retreive data from a server at the specified resource.\b\par
POST: \b0 POST requests are used to send data to the API server to create or update a resource.\b\par
PUT: \b0 PUT requests are used to send data to the API to update or create a resource.\b\par
HEAD: \b0 HEAD requests are useful for checking what a GET request will return before actually making a GET request.\b\par
DELETE: \b0 The DELETE method is used to delete the resource at the specified URL.\b\par
PATCH: \b0 It is similar to POST and PUT. The difference with PATCH is that we only apply partial modifications to the resource.\b\par
OPTIONS: \b0 An OPTIONS request should return data describing what other methods and operations the server supports at the given URL.\b\par
