Test Cases for API Testing:\par
\b0 Test cases of API testing are based on,\par
\b Return value based on input condition: \b0 it is relatively easy to test, as input can be defined and results can be authenticated\par
\b Does not return anything: \b0 When there is no return value, a behavior of API on the system to be checked\par
\b Trigger some other API/event/interrupt: \b0 If an output of an API triggers some event or interrupt, then those events and interrupt listeners should be tracked\par
\b Update data structure: \b0 Updating data structure will have some outcome or effect on the system, and that should be authenticated\par
