Difference between API testing and Unit testing:\par
API testing:\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Testers perform it.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}End-to-end functionality is tested.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Testers cannot access the source code.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Only API functions are tested.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}All functional issues are tested.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Broader in scope.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Test run after the build is created.\b\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Unit testing:\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Developers perform it.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Separate functionality is tested.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}A developer can access the source code.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}UI testing is also involved.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Only basic functionalities are tested.\par
