\b How to Test API:\par
\b0 API automation testing should cover following testing methods are:\b\par
Discovery testing: \b0 The test group should manually execute the set of calls documented in the API like verifying that a specific resource exposed by the API can be listed, created and deleted as appropriate.\par
\b Usability testing: \b0 This testing verifies whether the API is functional and user-friendly. And does API integrates well with another platform as well.\par
\b Security testing: \b0 This testing includes what type of authentication is required and whether sensitive data is encrypted over HTTP or both.\par
\b Automated testing: \b0 API testing should culminate in the creation of a set of scripts or a tool that can be used to execute the API regularly.\par
\b Documentation: \b0 The test team has to make sure that the documentation is adequate and provides enough information to interact with the API. Documentation should be a part of the final deliverable.\par
================================================================================\par
\b Best Practices of API Testing:\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 API Test cases should be grouped by test category.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}On top of each test, we should include the declarations of the APIs being called.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Parameters selection should be explicitly mentioned in the test case itself.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Prioritize API function calls so that it will be easy for testers to test.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Each test case should be as self-contained and independent from dependencies as possible.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Avoid \ldblquote test chaining\rdblquote  in our development.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Special care must be taken while handling one-time call functions like \f2\endash  Delete, CloseWindow, et\f1\lang16393 c.\f2\lang9\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Call sequencing should be performed and well planned\f1\lang16393 .\f2\lang9\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}To ensure complete test coverage, create API test cases for all possible input combinations of the API.\b\f1\par

